<inglise> Decision on Trade and Environment </inglise>
<eesti> vl56 RT II 1999, 22, 123 OTSUS KAUBANDUSE JA KESKKONNA KOHTA </eesti>
<inglise> Ministers, </inglise>
<eesti> Ministrid, </eesti>
<inglise> Meeting on the occasion of signing the Final Act Embodying the Results of the Uruguay Round of Multilateral Trade Negotiations at Marrakesh on 15 April 1994, </inglise>
<eesti> kohtudes Marrake&scaron;is 15. aprillil 1994. a mitmepoolsete kaubandusl&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste Uruguay vooru tulemusi &uuml;hendava l&otilde;ppakti allakirjutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Recalling the preamble of the Agreement establishing the World Trade Organization (WTO), which states that members' "relations in the field of trade and economic endeavour should be conducted with a view to raising standards of living, ensuring full employment and a large and steadily growing volume of real income and effective demand, and expanding the production of and trade in goods and services, while allowing for the optimal use of the world's resources in accordance with the objective of sustainable development, seeking both to protect and preserve the environment and to enhance the means for doing so in a manner consistent with their respective needs and concerns at different levels of economic development," </inglise>
<eesti> meelde tuletades Maailma Kaubandusorganisatsiooni (WTO) asutamislepingu preambulat, milles m&auml;rgitakse, et kaubandus- ja majandusp&uuml;&uuml;dluste vallas peaksid liikmed oma suhete korraldamisel juhinduma elatustaseme t&otilde;stmise, t&auml;ieliku t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive tagamise ning ulatusliku ja p&uuml;sivalt kasvava reaaltulu ja maksej&otilde;ulise n&otilde;udluse ning kaupade ja teenuste tootmise ning kaubavahetuse ja teenustekaubanduse laiendamise eesm&auml;rgist, v&otilde;imaldades maailma loodusvarade optimaalset kasutamist koosk&otilde;las s&auml;&auml;stva arengu p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega, p&uuml;&uuml;da keskkonda nii kaitsta kui ka s&auml;ilitada, ning t&otilde;hustades k&otilde;iki selleks vajalikke vahendeid viisil, mis sobib liikmete vastavate vajaduste ja huvidega majandusarengu eri tasemetel; </eesti>
<inglise> Noting: </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;rkides &auml;ra: </eesti>
<inglise> - the Rio Declaration on Environment and Development, Agenda 21, and its follow-up in GATT, as reflected in the statement of the Chairman of the Council of Representatives to the CONTRACTING PARTIES at their 48th Session in December 1992, as well as the work of the Group on Environmental Measures and International Trade, the Committee on Trade and Development, and the Council of Representatives; </inglise>
<eesti> - Rio de Janeiro keskkonna- ja arengudeklaratsiooni, Agenda 21 ja selle j&auml;rje GATTis, nagu seda on kajastatud LEPINGUOSALISTE esindajate n&otilde;ukogu esimehe avalduses k&otilde;nealuse n&otilde;ukogu 48. istungj&auml;rgul detsembris 1992, samuti keskkonnameetmete ja rahvusvahelise kaubanduse toimkonna, kaubandus- ja arengukomitee ning esindajate n&otilde;ukogu t&ouml;&ouml;; </eesti>
<inglise> - the work programme envisaged in the Decision on Trade in Services and the Environment; and </inglise>
<eesti> - teenustekaubandust ja keskkonda k&auml;sitlevas otsuses kajastatud t&ouml;&ouml;programmi; </eesti>
<inglise> - the relevant provisions of the Agreement on Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights, </inglise>
<eesti> - intellektuaalomandi &otilde;iguste kaubandusaspektide lepingu asjakohaseid s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> Considering that there should not be, nor need be, any policy contradiction between upholding and safeguarding an open, non-discriminatory and equitable multilateral trading system on the one hand, and acting for the protection of the environment, and the promotion of sustainable development on the other, </inglise>
<eesti> arvestades, et ei tohiks ega tarvitseks olla mingeid poliitilisi vastuolusid &uuml;helt poolt avatud, diskrimineerimisvaba ja erapooletu mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi toetamisel ja kaitsmisel ning teiselt poolt keskkonnakaitse ja s&auml;&auml;stva arengu edendamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Desiring to coordinate the policies in the field of trade and environment, and this without exceeding the competence of the multilateral trading system, which is limited to trade policies and those trade-related aspects of environmental policies which may result in significant trade effects for its members, </inglise>
<eesti> soovides koordineerida poliitikat kaubanduse ja keskkonna valdkonnas, &uuml;letamata seejuures mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi p&auml;devust, mis piirdub kaubanduspoliitika ja selliste keskkonnapoliitika kaubandusaspektidega, millest v&otilde;ivad tuleneda m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rsed kaubanduslikud tagaj&auml;rjed selle liikmetele, </eesti>
<inglise> Decide: </inglise>
<eesti> otsustavad: </eesti>
<inglise> - to direct the first meeting of the General Council of the WTO to establish a Committee on Trade and Environment open to all members of the WTO to report to the first biennial meeting of the Ministerial Conference after the entry into force of the WTO when the work and terms of reference of the Committee will be reviewed, in the light of recommendations of the Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> - teha WTO pean&otilde;ukogu esimesele istungile &uuml;lesandeks asutada kaubandus- ja keskkonnakomitee, mis on avatud k&otilde;ikidele WTO liikmetele, aruandmiseks ministrite konverentsi esimesel kahe aasta tagant toimuval istungil p&auml;rast WTO j&otilde;ustumist, mille k&auml;igus komitee t&ouml;&ouml; ja volitused komitee soovituste valgusel l&auml;bi vaadatakse, </eesti>
<inglise> - that the TNC Decision of 15 December 1993 which reads, in part, as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> - et 1993. aasta 15. detsembri kaubandusl&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste n&otilde;ukogu otsus, mis muu hulgas sedastab j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> "(a) to identify the relationship between trade measures and environmental measures, in order to promote sustainable development; </inglise>
<eesti> "a) m&auml;&auml;rata s&auml;&auml;stva arengu edendamiseks kindlaks kaubandus- ja keskkonnameetmete vaheline suhe; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) to make appropriate recommendations on whether any modifications of the provisions of the multilateral trading system are required, compatible with the open, equitable and non-discriminatory nature of the system, as regards, in particular: </inglise>
<eesti> b) teha asjakohaseid soovitusi selle kohta, kas mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi s&auml;tetesse on vaja teha muudatusi, mis sobivad kokku selle s&uuml;steemi avatud, erapooletu ja diskrimineerimisvaba olemusega, eriti mis puudutab: </eesti>
<inglise> - the need for rules to enhance positive interaction between trade and environmental measures, for the promotion of sustainable development, with special consideration to the needs of developing countries, in particular those of the least developed among them; and </inglise>
<eesti> - vajadust reeglite j&auml;rele, mis tugevdavad kaubandus- ja keskkonnameetmete vahelist positiivset koostoimet s&auml;&auml;stva arengu edendamiseks, v&otilde;ttes arvesse eriti arengumaade ja nende hulgas ise&auml;ranis v&auml;himarenenud maade vajadusi; </eesti>
<inglise> - the avoidance of protectionist trade measures, and the adherence to effective multilateral disciplines to ensure responsiveness of the multilateral trading system to environmental objectives set forth in Agenda 21 and the Rio Declaration, in particular Principle 12; and </inglise>
<eesti> - protektsionistlike kaubandusmeetmete v&auml;ltimist ja kinnipidamist m&otilde;jusatest mitmepoolsetest p&otilde;him&otilde;tetest tagamaks mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi reageerimist Agenda 21 ja Rio de Janeiro deklaratsioonile, eriti selle 12. p&otilde;him&otilde;ttes s&auml;testatud keskkonnakaitse eesm&auml;rkidele; </eesti>
<inglise> - surveillance of trade measures used for environmental purposes, of trade-related aspects of environmental measures which have significant trade affects, and of effective implementation of the multilateral disciplines governing those measures; &ldquo; </inglise>
<eesti> - keskkonnakaitse otstarbel v&otilde;etavate kaubandusmeetmete, kaubandust m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt m&otilde;jutavate keskkonnameetmete kaubandusaspektide ning nende meetmete suhtes kehtiva mitmepoolse korra t&otilde;husa t&auml;itmise j&auml;relevalvet"; </eesti>
<inglise> constitutes, along with the preambular language above, the terms of reference of the Committee on Trade and Environment, </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;rab koos eelneva preambulaga kaubandus- ja keskkonnakomitee volitused, </eesti>
<inglise> - that, within these terms of reference, and with the aim of making international trade and environmental policies mutually supportive, the Committee will initially address the following matters, in relation to which any relevant issue may be raised: </inglise>
<eesti> - et nende volituste raames ning selleks, et muuta rahvusvaheline kaubandus- ja keskkonnapoliitika teineteist vastastikku toetavaks, p&ouml;&ouml;rab komitee esialgu t&auml;helepanu j&auml;rgmistele asjadele, millega seoses v&otilde;idakse t&otilde;statada mis tahes asjakohaseid k&uuml;simusi: </eesti>
<inglise> - the relationship between the provisions of the multilateral trading system and trade measures for environmental purposes, including those pursuant to multilateral environmental agreements; </inglise>
<eesti> - suhe mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi s&auml;tete ja keskkonnaotstarbeliste kaubandusmeetmete, sealhulgas mitmepoolsete keskkonnalepingutega koosk&otilde;las olevate kaubandusmeetmete vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> - the relationship between environmental policies relevant to trade and environmental measures with significant trade effects and the provisions of the multilateral trading system; </inglise>
<eesti> - suhe kaubandust m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt m&otilde;jutavatele kaubandus- ja keskkonnameetmetele vastava keskkonnapoliitika ja mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi s&auml;tete vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> - the relationship between the provisions of the multilateral trading system and: </inglise>
<eesti> - suhe mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi s&auml;tete ja </eesti>
<inglise> (a) charges and taxes for environmental purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> a) keskkonnaotstarbeliste maksete ja maksude vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) requirements for environmental purposes relating to products, including standards and technical regulations, packaging, labelling and recycling; </inglise>
<eesti> b) toodetega seotud keskkonnan&otilde;uete, sealhulgas standardite ja tehniliste eeskirjade, pakendamise, etiketistamise ja teisese kasutamisega seotud n&otilde;uete vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> - the provisions of the multilateral trading system with respect to the transparency of trade measures used for environmental purposes and environmental measures and requirements which have significant trade effects; </inglise>
<eesti> - mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi s&auml;tted keskkonnaotstarbeliste kaubandusmeetmete selguse suhtes ja kaubandust m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt m&otilde;jutavad keskkonnameetmed ja -n&otilde;uded; </eesti>
<inglise> - the relationship between the dispute settlement mechanisms in the multilateral trading system and those found in multilateral environmental agreements; </inglise>
<eesti> - suhe mitmepoolse kaubanduss&uuml;steemi vaidluste lahendamise mehhanismide ja mitmepoolsetes keskkonnalepingutes leiduvate vaidluste lahendamise mehhanismide vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> - the effect of environmental measures on market access, especially in relation to developing countries, in particular to the least developed among them, and environmental benefits of removing trade restrictions and distortions; </inglise>
<eesti> - keskkonnameetmete m&otilde;ju turulep&auml;&auml;sule, eriti arengumaade ja nende hulgas ise&auml;ranis v&auml;himarenenud maade suhtes, ning kaubanduspiirangute ja -moonutuste k&otilde;rvaldamise kasu keskkonnale; </eesti>
<inglise> - the issue of exports of domestically prohibited goods, </inglise>
<eesti> - siseturul keelatud kaupade ekspordi k&uuml;simus, </eesti>
<inglise> - that the Committee on Trade and Environment will consider the work programme envisaged in the Decision on Trade in Services and the Environment and the relevant provisions of the Agreement on Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights as an integral part of its work, within the above terms of reference, </inglise>
<eesti> - et kaubandus- ja keskkonnakomitee v&otilde;tab arvesse teenustekaubandust ja keskkonda k&auml;sitlevas otsuses ette n&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;programmi ning intellektuaalomandi &otilde;iguste kaubandusaspektide lepingu asjakohaseid s&auml;tteid kui oma t&ouml;&ouml; lahutamatut osa eespool nimetatud volituste piires, </eesti>
<inglise> - that, pending the first meeting of the General Council of the WTO, the work of the Committee on Trade and Environment should be carried out by a Sub-Committee of the Preparatory Committee of the World Trade Organization (PCWTO), open to all members of the PCWTO, </inglise>
<eesti> - et kuni WTO pean&otilde;ukogu esimese istungini peaks kaubandus- ja keskkonnakomitee t&ouml;&ouml;d tegema Maailma Kaubandusorganisatsiooni ettevalmistuskomitee allkomitee, mis on avatud k&otilde;ikidele WTO ettevalmistuskomitee liikmetele, </eesti>
<inglise> - to invite the Sub-Committee of the Preparatory Committee, and the Committee on Trade and Environment when it is established, to provide input to the relevant bodies in respect of appropriate arrangements for relations with inter-governmental and non-governmental organizations referred to in Article V of the WTO. </inglise>
<eesti> - kutsuda &uuml;les ettevalmistuskomitee allkomiteed ning kaubandus- ja keskkonnakomiteed, kui see on loodud, andma oma panuse asjaomastele organitele suhete korraldamiseks WTO lepingu V artiklis viidatud riikidevaheliste ja valitsusv&auml;liste organisatsioonidega. </eesti>
 